## [2026-01-17] - Document description vs content Field Distinction for Linear Projects

### Added
- **"Understanding Project Description vs Content" section** documenting two distinct text fields:
  - `description` (NON_NULL) - Short summary/tagline for project cards and lists
  - `content` (String) - Full markdown content for Project Overview tab
- API field type documentation from GraphQL introspection
- "When to Use Each Field" guidance
- Anti-pattern example (WRONG vs RIGHT usage)
- Content truncation behavior documentation:
  - `get-project`: content truncated to 1000 chars by default
  - `list-projects`: content truncated to 500 chars by default
  - `fullContent: true` parameter to get untruncated content
- Project template `templateData` JSON structure guidance
- **Usage Examples:**
  - "Get Project with Full Content" example showing `fullContent: true` parameter
  - "Create Project with Description and Content" example showing both fields

### Changed
- Updated Projects table Key Parameters:
  - `get-project`: Added `fullContent` (optional, default: false)
  - `list-projects`: Added `fullContent` (optional, default: false)

### Context
- Wrappers `get-project.ts` and `list-projects.ts` were updated to expose `content` field
- Both wrappers now have `fullContent` parameter for truncation control
- This documentation update closes the gap preventing users from knowing about the `content` field
- Prevents anti-pattern of putting full markdown in `description` field

---

