## [Previous Entry] - Documentation Enhancement

### Added
- List Projects example in Common Operations section (after List Issues, before Update Issue)
  - Shows how to call listProjects.execute({})
  - Uses standard ROOT pattern with npx tsx
  - Includes 2>/dev/null to suppress MCP debug logs
  - Documents return value: projects array with id, name, description, lead, status fields

### Enhanced
- Update Issue example now includes project parameter
  - Added: `project: 'Agentic Development'  // Optional - Project name or ID`
  - Added to Key parameters list: `- project (optional) - Project name or ID`

### Context
- Fixed list-projects.ts parsing bug (rawData.content vs rawData.projects)
- Added CLI project parameter support to .claude/bin/linear.ts
- Wrappers always supported these features; examples now document them for user discovery
